  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7\u0db8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "European gas prices highest since March",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "European natural gas prices hit a three-month high amid ongoing concerns about a lack of Russian supplies and EU efforts to fill storage facilities ahead of the start of the hot season.",
        "The Netherlands' TTF trading center says it will rise 6.4% to $1,630 per thousand cubic meters by August. Intercontinental exchange data in London also showed an increase to 149.15 euros ($155.05) per megawatt hour domestically. It was the first time since March 10 that natural gas prices exceeded that level.",
        "On June 14, Russian gas exporter Gazprom cut supplies to Germany via the Nord Stream pipeline by 60%, citing technical problems due to Western sanctions over Ukraine. Following the decision, Germany called for a reduction in gas consumption in the country, and several other EU countries announced measures to help use less gas, including reviving coal-fired power plants."
      ],
